      "clean_strategic": "Casablanca Aménagement mobility program between Casablanca and Nouaceur includes major road widenings/new links (e.g., widening RR320 Route d’Azemmour, doubling RN1 segments, new interchanges) with global budget 2 billion MAD (Casa Aménagement ). A separate repor",
      "clean_population": "Arrondissement Hay-Hassani population 537,509 (2024 census/RGPH 2024), area 40.81 km² (City Population – Hay-Hassani ). Casablanca city population 3,215,935 (2024 census/RGPH 2024) (City Population – Casablanca ). HCP published an XLS ‘Population légale’ dataset referencing RGPH 2024 and showing Arrondissement Hay-Hassani totals (file download) (HCP ).",
      "clean_traffic": "National road traffic count reference: Morocco’s CNER publishes an annual “Recueil du trafic routier 2023” (traffic count compendium; requires extracting the relevant counting station on the Route d’El Jadida/RN1 corridor) (CNER PDF ). Major Casablanca highway project (A31) reported with initial traffic estimated ~20,000 vehicles/day (context for Greater Casablanca ring-road traffic) (Ecofin Agency ). Official road network maps available from Morocco’s Ministry of Equipment and Water (useful to confirm road classification around Route d’El Jadida/RN1/RR320) (Ministry of Equipment – Cartes routières ).",
      "clean_competitors": "The Petrom IST-FDS Istiraha Fleche du Sud offers car wash (lavage automobile) and oil change (vidange d'huile) services. Nearby on same road (Route El Jadida, Ferme Bretonne): Shell Oasis station with car wash. Afriquia station in Hay Hassani Secteur 207 (~2km?). Total station in Hay Hassani Secteur 207. Sparse specific garages/tire shops identified within 2km (e.g., Pièces Autos Saad ElKhair in Hay Hassani); area has general auto parts but no major quick-fit centers verified close by.City-Info Petrom, City-Info Shell",
      "clean_infrastructure": "Casablanca Aménagement mobility program between Casablanca and Nouaceur includes major road widenings/new links (e.g., widening RR320 Route d’Azemmour, doubling RN1 segments, new interchanges) with global budget 2 billion MAD (Casa Aménagement ). A separate reported road project aims to ease traffic between Hay Hassani and Dar Bouazza with first phase budget 100 million MAD (target completion Oct 2025) (Yabiladi ). Mohammed V Airport new terminal project: investment about 15 billion MAD, capacity +20M pax/year, targeted operational 2029 (Airports 2030 strategy) (African Pilot Magazine ).",
      "clean_commercial": "The station is in/near Ferme Bretonne on the Route d’El Jadida corridor, an axis connecting Casablanca toward the airport/Nouaceur and retail zones (incl. Marjane areas mentioned as part of the Route d’El Jadida commercial corridor) (Masscom Global ). Industrial activity is present in Hay Hassani, including Zone industrielle Diar Lissasfa (example distributor address in Lissasfa Hay Hassani) (Mactac Graphics ).",
      "clean_transport": "Road access: the site is on Route d’El Jadida, a main southwest axis linking Casablanca toward Nouaceur/Mohammed V Airport and beyond (context from Casablanca–Nouaceur mobility program) (Casa Aménagement ). Public transport in the broader area is served by Casa Tramway/Casa Busway network (official site for lines/schedules) (CasaTramway ). Hay Hassani can be reached from Casa Voyageurs by tram + bus (Rome2Rio itinerary referencing CasaTramway) (Rome2Rio ). Airport proximity proxy: accommodations in Ferme Bretonne report Mohammed V International Airport about 22 km away (useful distance indicator) (Agoda ).",
      "market_intel": "Ferme Bretonne is a calm, green, gated residential neighborhood in arrondissement Hay Hassani, Casablanca-Settat, characterized by luxury apartments and villas with palm trees, adjacent to Oasis. Hay Hassani arrondissement has a population of 537,509 (RGPH 2024 HCP census), up from ~468,000 in 2014, over 25.91 km² (~20,735 hab/km²), one of Casablanca's most active residential real estate markets with ~3,800 transactions in 2024 and high property prices (~16,000 DH/m² in Ferme Bretonne). Income levels are upper-middle to high, indicated by luxury developments and strong Airbnb market (median ~$689/month). Landmarks/developments: near OCP offices, CFC (Casa Finance City?), Aeria Mall.Wikipedia RGPH 2024), HCP, Medias24, Green Corners",
      "competitor_analysis": "The Petrom IST-FDS Istiraha Fleche du Sud offers car wash (lavage automobile) and oil change (vidange d'huile) services. Nearby on same road (Route El Jadida, Ferme Bretonne): Shell Oasis station with car wash. Afriquia station in Hay Hassani Secteur 207 (~2km?). Total station in Hay Hassani Secteur 207. Sparse specific garages/tire shops identified within 2km (e.g., Pièces Autos Saad ElKhair in Hay Hassani); area has general auto parts but no major quick-fit centers verified close by.City-Info Petrom, City-Info Shell",
      "traffic_access": "Located on Route El Jadida (N1 towards El Jadida), a major regional highway serving southern Casablanca suburbs, with good accessibility. Casabus line 19 serves Hay Hassani area. Local congestion reported (e.g., winter traffic jams on nearby boulevards like Adrarissa, Omar al Khayam). No specific traffic volumes or major widening/highway projects verified for this stretch.Waze, Facebook local, Moovit Casabus",
      "infrastructure_new": "Ongoing luxury residential projects: Terrafino Ferme Bretonne (delivery Dec 2025), Missimi Living Hay Hassani, Green Corner II. Near OCP (Office Chérifien des Phosphates) facilities driving commercial activity. No industrial zones or major government infrastructure investments specifically verified nearby; CRI CS reports general regional investments.Instagram Terrafino, Levana Properties, Medias24",
      "commercial_context_new": "Proximity to OCP offices, CFC/Casa Finance City (5min), Aeria Mall, CAFC. Local schools (Ecole ElFarabi Ferme Bretonne, Ecole de la Ferme Bretonne). Hay Hassani Market (kissariat souk), Health Center Hay Hassani, Hôpital Al Hassani. Commercial shops/locals along Route El Jadida.Booking, Telecontact, YouTube Market",
      "fleet_potential": "Station Taxi Hay Hassani nearby. Car rental agencies in Hay Hassani. Vehicle inspection (controle technique) centers nearby e.g., DEKRA Oulfa (Boulevard Oued Sebou, ~3-4km). No specific delivery/logistics hubs or taxi ranks directly at Ferme Bretonne verified, but urban area supports daily fleet traffic.Waze Taxi, Dekra, Kayak Rentals",
      "key_insight": "Prime upper-middle class residential area with high real estate activity and good traffic on Route El Jadida supports quick-service bay potential, especially with limited verified competitors beyond basic station washes; fleet from taxis, rentals, and OCP drives demand. New residential projects will increase local car ownership."
