      "clean_traffic": "Road context: Aïn Harrouda is a key highway junction at the north entrance to Casablanca, serving Casablanca highway access and north-south transit (Morocco World News ). Traffic volumes: the Aïn Harrouda interchange corridor is reported at ~140,000 vehicles/day (article) (Express TV ). Road classification: the site sits in the Casablanca-Settat coastal corridor connecting Casablanca and Mohammedia and linking to the A1 Rabat–Casablanca motorway; A101 is listed as “Pénétrante d’Ain Harrouda” in Morocco’s motorway network references (secondary reference) .",
