      "competitors": "Note: within-2km competitor verification is constrained without a map-API query; below are verifiable nearby-brand station entries with published coordinates/addresses from first-party station network pages.\n\n• Afriquia ‘MARJANE AIN SEBAA’ (Afriquia network listing provides coordinates 33.59653249, -7.53076345; Ain Sebaa / Marjane context—potential competitor in the broader NE Casablanca area) (Afriquia – Stations services (https://www.afriquia.ma/reseau/stations-services)).\n• Afriquia ‘GRANDE CEINTURE I/II’ (Afriquia listing provides coordinates 33.5941606, -7.5451923; ‘Ain Sebaa’ — potential competitor in NE Casablanca) (Afriquia – Stations services (https://www.afriquia.ma/reseau/stations-services)).\n• Afriquia ‘ROUTE DE RABAT’ (Afriquia listing indicates “Route de Rabat Km 7 Arrondissement Ain Sbaa, Casablanca” with coordinates 33.60392289, -7.54750171—potential competitor corridor feeding the same submarket) (Afriquia – Stations services (https://www.afriquia.ma/reseau/stations-services)).\n\n(Additional nearby stations likely exist—Shell/Total/Winxo/Oilybia/etc.—but were not included here because we did not obtain verifiable within-2km coordinates from authoritative sources in this run.)",
      "infrastructure": "• Zenata Urban Development Project (new city / infrastructure): EIB project page states development works for “nouvelle ville de Zenata” on 1,660 ha near Casablanca, with total cost ~EUR 800m and proposed EIB finance EUR 150m, and status “Signed 13/11/2014” (European Investment Bank – Zenata Urban Development Project (https://www.eib.org/en/projects/pipelines/all/20120617)).\n• Road logistics infrastructure tied to Zenata corridor: CasablancaCity.ma (official municipal portal) lists “Route de Zenata et travaux sur axes pénétrants” including completion of a dedicated truck corridor linking the port to the logistics zone (improving congestion, sidewalks, lighting, landscaping) (CasablancaCity.ma – Ouvrages et aménagements routiers (https://www.casablancacity.ma/fr/article/253/ouvrages-et-amenagements-routiers-pour-fluidifier-le-trafic)).\n• Port–Aïn Sebaâ coastal road (freight mobility): Le360 reports a 4.5 km “route maritime” opened to connect the Port of Casablanca to the coastal Casablanca–Mohammedia road via Rond-point Mimosas at Aïn Sebaâ, with budget 830 million dirhams, and mentions a subsequent link toward the Zenata logistics zone (Le360 Français (https://fr.le360.ma/societe/une-aubaine-pour-les-routiers-decouvrez-la-nouvelle-route-maritime-desservant-le-port-de-casablanca_EZGOJJFS65AI5HM2MKPLEGZH3I/)).",
      "commercial": "• Zenata Mall (planned / promoted): Visit Casablanca describes “Zenata Mall” as located “au cœur de l’Éco-Cité Zenata” and presents contact details, indicating a planned major retail anchor in the Zenata area (Visit Casablanca – Zenata Mall Mohammedia (https://visitcasablanca.ma/pois/zenata-mall-mohammedia-2/)).\n• IKEA Zenata (constructed retail project): TGCC (major Moroccan contractor) lists a “Centre Commercial IKEA Zenata” realization in Casablanca for “Marjane Holding – Zenata Commercial Project,” confirming existence of a major retail development in Zenata (TGCC – Centre Commercial IKEA Zenata (https://www.tgcc.ma/realisations/centre-commercial-ikea-zenata/)).\n• Industrial/logistics orientation of Zenata project: A public EIB document about Zenata references planned activity zones including “un centre commercial, un port sec et une zone industrielle,” supporting proximity to large-scale commercial/industrial zoning (European Investment Bank document (PDF) related to Zenata (https://www.eib.org/attachments/registers/58846810.pdf)).\n• Commercial rent levels (market listings, indicative not official statistics): Casablanca commercial lease listings show monthly asking rents in the tens of thousands of MAD for mid-to-large spaces (e.g., 28,000–98,000 MAD/month examples), useful only as market indications, not official benchmarks (Mubawab – locaux commerciaux à louer Casablanca (https://www.mubawab.ma/fr/st/casablanca/locaux-a-louer)).",
      "transport": "Public transport near Route de Zenata (bus/train/tram):\n• Moovit lists bus lines 900, 608, 23 and train lines TNR, AL ATLAS, TGL passing near “Route De Zenata,” and indicates a nearby light rail station “Préfecture De Aïn Sebaa” (~15 min walk) and train station “Aïn-Sebaâ” (~24 min walk) (Moovit – Route De Zenata (https://moovitapp.com/index/en/public_transit-Route_De_Zenata-Casablanca-street_13711571-5496)).\n\nRegional multimodal context:\n• Casainvest describes Zenata eco-city as positioned at the crossroads of road, railway, logistics and airway infrastructures, indicating connectivity to major transport corridors (Casainvest – Zenata Eco City (https://casainvest.ma/en/projets/zenata-eco-city)).\n\n(Precise road distances from the PTM-11 GPS point to Mohammed V International Airport or specific highway interchanges were not computed in a verifiable way during this run.)",
      "additional": "• Zenata Eco-City project promoter: Société d’Aménagement de Zenata (SAZ) is listed as the promoter/borrower for the EIB “Zenata Urban Development Project,” indicating institutional backing and formal project governance (European Investment Bank – Zenata Urban Development Project (https://www.eib.org/en/projects/pipelines/all/20120617)).\n• Zenata Eco-City strategic positioning: Casablanca Finance & Investment promotion site describes Zenata as being at a crossroads of “road, railway, logistics and airway infrastructures,” supporting the site’s broader logistics/through-traffic context (Casainvest – Zenata Eco City (https://casainvest.ma/en/projets/zenata-eco-city)).",
