      "clean_population": "Latest official census (RGPH 2024) – Casablanca city & relevant arrondissements: · Casablanca City population: 3,215,935 (2024 census); previous 3,357,173 (2014 census) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). · Arrondissement Aïn Sebaâ population: 155,828 (2024 census) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). · Arrondissement Sidi Bernoussi population: 154,919 (2024 census) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). · Arrondissement Hay Mohammadi population: 104,232 (2024 census) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). · Arrondissement Sidi Moumen population: 551,443 (2024 census) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). Population structure (Casablanca city – 2014 census): CityPopulation provides age-group and gender breakdowns for 2014 (e.g., males 1,646,761; females 1,694,289; 0–14 years 787,040; 15–64 years 2,334,631; 65+ 219,378) (CityPopulation – Casablanca City ). (Income/household income indicators at arrondissement/commune level were not found in verifiable official sources during this run.)",
      "clean_traffic": "Route de Zenata corridor – road improvements (official city portal): · CasablancaCity.ma lists “Route de Zenata et travaux sur axes pénétrants,” including completion of a dedicated heavy-truck corridor linking the Port of Casablanca to the Zenata logistics zone, plus roadworks (networks, sidewalks, public lighting, landscaping) (CasablancaCity.ma – Ouvrages et aménagements routiers ). Traffic counts used in engineering study (2012) – Port–Zenata heavy-vehicle corridor & RR322/N9: · A road project report (Port of Casablanca → Zenata logistics zone) documents TMJA on the heavy-vehicle corridor: 4,130 PL/day in 2012 (and notes conversion assumption to 8,260 veh/day using equivalence coefficient 2) (Scribd – “rapporte de projet routier” ). · The same report includes hourly traffic table for RN9 PK30 (2012) (e.g., 18:00 peak 1,740 veh/h in the table) and references RR322 count posts used for design calculations (Scribd – “rapporte de projet routier” ). (We did not find an official Moroccan open-data traffic count station specifically at the provided GPS point during this run.)",
