      "clean_infrastructure": "· Zenata Urban Development Project (new city / infrastructure): EIB project page states development works for “nouvelle ville de Zenata” on 1,660 ha near Casablanca, with total cost ~EUR 800m and proposed EIB finance EUR 150m, and status “Signed 13/11/2014” (European Investment Bank – Zenata Urban Development Project ). · Road logistics infrastructure tied to Zenata corridor: CasablancaCity.ma (official municipal portal) lists “Route de Zenata et travaux sur axes pénétrants” including completion of a dedicated truck corridor linking the port to the logistics zone (improving congestion, sidewalks, lighting, landscaping) (CasablancaCity.ma – Ouvrages et aménagements routiers ). · Port–Aïn Sebaâ coastal road (freight mobility): Le360 reports a 4.5 km “route maritime” opened to connect the Port of Casablanca to the coastal Casablanca–Mohammedia road via Rond-point Mimosas at Aïn Sebaâ, with budget 830 million dirhams, and mentions a subsequent link toward the Zenata logistics zone (Le360 Français ).",
