      "clean_transport": "Public transport near Route de Zenata (bus/train/tram): · Moovit lists bus lines 900, 608, 23 and train lines TNR, AL ATLAS, TGL passing near “Route De Zenata,” and indicates a nearby light rail station “Préfecture De Aïn Sebaa” (~15 min walk) and train station “Aïn-Sebaâ” (~24 min walk) (Moovit – Route De Zenata ). Regional multimodal context: · Casainvest describes Zenata eco-city as positioned at the crossroads of road, railway, logistics and airway infrastructures, indicating connectivity to major transport corridors (Casainvest – Zenata Eco City ). (Precise road distances from the PTM-11 GPS point to Mohammed V International Airport or specific highway interchanges were not computed in a verifiable way during this run.)",
      "market_intel": "The PTM-11 Al Karam Petromin station is located on Route de Rabat near Ain Sebaa (33.61534° N, 7.50426° W), in the NE Zenata corridor, an emerging eco-city area planned for 300,000 residents. Surrounding Ain Sebaa arrondissement has 155,828 inhabitants (RGPH 2024 census) at 10,156/km² density over 15.34 km²; nearby Ain Harrouda commune 60,804 hab. Area mixes residential, industrial zones; income levels typical of east Casablanca (working-class, no specific data found), with high urbanization. Major landmarks: OFPPT college, local mosque. HCP RGPH 2024 via CityPopulation, Mapcarta, Arab Urban Development.",
      "competitor_analysis": "Within ~2km: Zenata Pneus (Goodyear tires, Route Zenata km8.4); Shell Zenata (km9.4 Route Mohamadia Ain Sebaa, car wash); Shell Grande Route Al Amal (Rte Rabat Ain Sebaa Priquest, car wash); Afriquia Rte Rabat km7 Ain Sbaa; auto repairs on Rte Zenata (Société Chamaa Pièces Auto, City Car Repair, Star Auto Afric, Auto Fath Allah, Auto 35, Carrosserie Phenix). No confirmed quick-service bays at majors; fragmented local garages/tire shops. Shell, Afriquia, Yandex Maps, Telecontact.",
      "traffic_access": "Served by Route de Rabat (N1 to Rabat), Route Zenata (to Mohammedia/Ain Harrouda), proximity to A1 highway and port-Casablanca-Zenata logistics road (21km, completed ~2016 for heavy trucks). High traffic volumes due to port/logistics access; occasional congestion (e.g., landslides). Good accessibility via ONCF Ain Sebaa train station (2km). No recent widening projects noted. Le Matin, Mapcarta.",
      "infrastructure_new": "Zenata Eco-City (1,830ha, ongoing since 2016, $2.2B investment): residential, university campus, 300-bed hospital, 115k m² commercial center, 4.7km² parks. New integrated industrial/logistics park (379ha, 2.8B MAD budget, 25k jobs expected; society created Nov 2025 by ANP, ONCF, Region Casablanca-Settat, AMDL, SAZ). Govt/EU/EIB funding. Medias24, Casainvest, Arab Urban.",
      "commercial_context_new": "Zenata Mall (under development, one of Africa's largest, with Ikea/Marjane); Hôpital Privé Casablanca Ain Sebaa (220+ beds); offices/business centers (Regus Ain Harrouda/Nozha Ain Sebaa); schools (Ecole Notre Dame Ain Sebaa, OFPPT); local markets/souks nearby. Drives daily commuter/worker traffic. Bladi, Akdital, Regus.",
      "fleet_potential": "Zone logistique Zenata (SNTL-managed, expanding to 323ha; delivery/logistics operators); DEKRA Ain Sbaa controle technique center (Av Mly Slimane); ONCF Ain Sebaa station supports commuter/taxi fleets; heavy truck traffic to port/Zenata platforms. High fleet potential from logistics growth. DEKRA, Casainvest.",
      "key_insight": "Prime location in booming Zenata Eco-City/logistics hub with growing population/traffic, but faces local tire/car wash competition; quick-service bay could capture underserved fleet/professional demand amid infrastructure boom."
