      "population_data": "Aïn Harrouda (Urban Commune, Prefecture Mohammédia, Casablanca-Settat) – Census population\n\n- Population (RGPH 2024): 60,804 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n- Population (RGPH 2014): 62,420 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n- Population (RGPH 2004): 41,853 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n- Population (RGPH 1994): 27,741 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n\nDemographic structure (from RGPH 2014 as compiled on CityPopulation; source credited to HCP)\n- Gender (2014): Males 30,804, Females 31,420 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n- Broad age groups (2014): 0–14 18,014; 15–64 41,652; 65+ 2,558 (CityPopulation – Aïn Harrouda admin table (https://citypopulation.de/en/morocco/grandcasablancasettat/admin/mohamm%C3%A9dia/3710103__a%C3%AFn_harrouda/)).\n\nSocioeconomic / income indicators: I did not locate a commune-level income/poverty dataset from an official publisher within the research time window.",
      "traffic_data": "- Road classification (provincial roads): Morocco’s Ministry of Equipment road network map for Préfecture Mohammadia shows the presence of provincial road P3004 in the Ain Harrouda area (map legend includes “Route provinciale”) (Ministry of Equipment – Mohammadia road network map PDF (https://www.equipement.gov.ma/Infrastructures-Routieres/Reseau-Routier-du-Royaume/Documents/Cartes-2019/Provinciales%20FR/6_Grand%20Casablanca-Settat/Pr%C3%A9fecture%20Mohammadia%20FR%20A3.pdf)).\n- Traffic volumes (motorway corridor near site): ADM states the Mohammedia Ouest ↔ Ain Harrouda section has traffic “avoisinant 140,000 véhicules/jour” (ADM press release – Ain Harrouda node completion (https://www.adm.co.ma/fr/communiques-de-presse/adm-annonce-la-fin-des-travaux-de-transformation-du-noeud-autoroutier-de-ain)).\n- Planned / delivered road improvements: ADM describes redesign including full separation of traffic flows and additional connections, as part of the 750 MDH project (ADM press release – Ain Harrouda node completion (https://www.adm.co.ma/fr/communiques-de-presse/adm-annonce-la-fin-des-travaux-de-transformation-du-noeud-autoroutier-de-ain)).\n\nNote: I did not find an official traffic count (AADT) dataset specifically for P3004 itself; only verified motorway-section traffic from ADM.",
      "competitors": "Within ~2 km of the provided site coordinates (33.6332131, -7.4581042), the following branded fuel competitors publish location details:\n\n- Afriquia AIN HARROUDA (competitor station). Address “Croisement Route Nationale N1 et Boulevard de la Palestine, Aïn Harrouda” with coordinates 33.63425349, -7.45385566 (Afriquia – Stations services (https://www.afriquia.ma/reseau/stations-services)).\n- Shell ‘AIN HARROUDA’ (competitor station). Shell’s station locator lists a station page for AIN HARROUDA (location details hosted on Shell’s locator) (Shell station locator – AIN HARROUDA (https://find.shell.com/ma/fuel/10124945-ain-harrouda/fr_CI)).\n\nNote: Other nearby stations (TotalEnergies/Winxo/Petrom/Oilibya) likely exist in the Casablanca–Mohammedia corridor, but I did not find first‑party pages with precise coordinates within the research time window.",
